SauceDemo Playwright — Multi-Browser Parallel Suite

An end-to-end test suite built with **Playwright for Java** that validates
the complete SauceDemo purchase journey across Chromium, Firefox, and WebKit
simultaneously — with zero code changes between browsers.

---

## 📋 Project Overview

This project migrates a Selenium WebDriver suite to Microsoft Playwright,
replacing WebDriver + WebDriverManager with Playwright's self-contained
browser engine. All three browser types — Chromium, Firefox, and WebKit
(Safari's engine) — are bundled inside the Playwright dependency. No
external driver downloads are needed.

Tests run in parallel using TestNG's `parallel="tests"` with `ThreadLocal<Page>`
ensuring each browser thread gets a fully isolated Page instance.

---

## 🌐 Browsers Tested

| Browser | Engine | How it runs |
|---|---|---|
| **Chromium** | Blink | `playwright.chromium().launch()` |
| **Firefox** | Gecko | `playwright.firefox().launch()` |
| **WebKit** | WebKit | `playwright.webkit().launch()` |

---

## ✅ Test Scenarios

| # | Test | What it validates |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | `testLogin` | Valid credentials navigate to the Products page |
| 2 | `testAddToCart` | Cart badge updates to "1" after adding the backpack |
| 3 | `testGoToCartPage` | Cart icon opens the cart page |
| 4 | `testCheckoutStart` | Checkout button opens the information form |
| 5 | `testCheckoutInformation` | Form submission navigates to the order overview |
| 6 | `testFinishCheckout` | Finish button displays the confirmation message |



## 🏗️ Architecture

src/test/java/
├── base/
│   └── BaseTest.java         # Playwright lifecycle + ThreadLocal<Page>
├── pages/
│   ├── LoginPage.java
│   ├── InventoryPage.java
│   ├── CartPage.java
│   ├── CheckoutInfoPage.java
│   ├── CheckoutOverviewPage.java
│   └── ConfirmationPage.java
└── tests/
└── OnlineOrderTest.java  # 6 priority-ordered @Test methods


## 🛠️ Tools & Technologies

| Tool | Version | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| **Java** | 21 | Core programming language |
| **Playwright** | 1.44.0 | Browser automation — replaces Selenium entirely |
| **TestNG** | 7.11.0 | Test framework and parallel execution |
| **Maven** | — | Dependency management and build |

---

## 💡 Concepts Demonstrated

- **Playwright vs Selenium** — `page.fill()`, `page.click()`,
  `page.waitForLoadState()` replace `findElement`, `sendKeys`, `Thread.sleep()`
- **ThreadLocal isolation** — parallel browsers never share Page state
- **`@Parameters` + XML suites** — browser choice driven entirely by config
- **`setSlowMo()`** — global action pacing replaces per-step `Thread.sleep()`
- **`waitForLoadState()`** — event-driven waits replace implicit timeouts
- **WebKit support** — Safari's engine tested without owning a Mac

---

## 🚀 How to Run

```bash
# Install Playwright browsers — one-time setup
mvn exec:java -e -D exec.mainClass=com.microsoft.playwright.CLI -D exec.args="install"

# Run all browsers in parallel
mvn test

# Run one browser
mvn test -Dsuite=testng-chromium
mvn test -Dsuite=testng-firefox
mvn test -Dsuite=testng-webkit
```
